    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A dwarf clad in thermal wraps and chain, carrying an axe and a heavy shield. Heitfolk sentries guard the geothermal tunnel entrances that sustain their people. They are disciplined and wary but not hostile — their purpose is defense, not aggression. They will challenge strangers firmly but can be reasoned with.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Axe Strike</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): 7 damage.</li><li><strong>Shield Shove</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): 3 damage + target Pushed 2 squares.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Tunnel-Kin:</strong> Cannot be flanked. +2 to all tests in enclosed spaces.</li></ul><p><strong>ENCOUNTER CONTEXT</strong></p><p>Beat 20. Social fallback only — extremely unlikely to be used in combat. If the party helped Hildvarð Bruneson in Beat 17, the Heitfolk recognize and welcome them immediately. If not, the Sentry challenges them: a Hard TN 14 Presence test or clear explanation of purpose avoids combat. Hildvarð can be found with the patrol if the party reaches out peacefully.</p><p>If combat does occur (party aggressive or failed social), deploy 2–4 sentries. They fight defensively, attempting to push intruders away from the tunnel entrance rather than kill.</p>",
